    {
      "id": "mn88nr7qbc0wy73ospp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 50,
      "y": 1020,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 17,
      "strokeColor": "#868e96",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "text": "Legend:  Blue = Shared / Small Tenants     Yellow = Dedicated / Large Tenant     Green = Storage     Red = StarRocks     Purple = Kafka",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 29,
      "version": 1,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "mn88nw32ham6y7my9rw",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 50,
      "y": 1060,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 110,
      "strokeColor": "#495057",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "text": "Key Design Decisions:\n1. Shared FE layer — all tenants go through same 3-node FE HA cluster (no data stored in FE for Iceberg external catalog)\n2. CN pool segregation — small tenants share \"default\" warehouse; large tenants get dedicated warehouse with own CN pool\n3. Data fully in S3/Iceberg — CN nodes are stateless compute; local SSD is cache only → easy horizontal scaling\n4. New small tenant = just add Kafka Connect connector + Iceberg DB, no StarRocks infra change\n5. New large tenant = provision dedicated CN pool (new K8s nodegroup) + create StarRocks warehouse\n6. FP Async unchanged — Iceberg pipeline is a parallel consumer path, not a replacement of YugabyteDB/ClickHouse writes",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 30,
      "version": 1,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    }
